  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">For the Lady of Starfall, see <a href=\"/index.php/Clarisse_Dayne\" title=\"Clarisse Dayne\">Clarisse Dayne</a>.</div>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Osgrey\" title=\"House Osgrey\"><img alt=\"House Osgrey.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/a/a7/House_Osgrey.svg/50px-House_Osgrey.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/a/a7/House_Osgrey.svg/75px-House_Osgrey.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/a/a7/House_Osgrey.svg/100px-House_Osgrey.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\">Clarice Osgrey</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Osgrey\" title=\"House Osgrey\"><img alt=\"House Osgrey.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/a/a7/House_Osgrey.svg/50px-House_Osgrey.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/a/a7/House_Osgrey.svg/75px-House_Osgrey.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/a/a7/House_Osgrey.svg/100px-House_Osgrey.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Clarice_Osgrey_02.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Clarice Osgrey 02.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/c/cc/Clarice_Osgrey_02.png/350px-Clarice_Osgrey_02.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"350\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/c/cc/Clarice_Osgrey_02.png/525px-Clarice_Osgrey_02.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/c/cc/Clarice_Osgrey_02.png/700px-Clarice_Osgrey_02.png 2x\" /></a><div>Clarice Osgrey</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\nMistress of the Queen's household</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiances</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Osgrey\" title=\"House Osgrey\">House Osgrey</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Peake\" title=\"House Peake\">House Peake</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">House Targaryen</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Reach\" title=\"Reach\">Reach</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Spouse</th><td>\nUnknown</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Lover</th><td>\nLord <a href=\"/index.php/George_Graceford\" title=\"George Graceford\">George Graceford</a> <small>(rumored)</small><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i> (mentioned)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Clarice Osgrey</b> was a noblewoman of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Osgrey\" title=\"House Osgrey\">House Osgrey</a> during the reign of King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_III_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon III Targaryen\">Aegon III Targaryen</a>. She was mistress of the households of Aegon's two queens, <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaera_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaera Targaryen\">Jaehaera Targaryen</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Daenaera_Velaryon\" title=\"Daenaera Velaryon\">Daenaera Velaryon</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Character\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Character</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Behind_the_Scenes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Behind the Scenes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Character\">Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Clarice_Osgrey&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>According to <a href=\"/index.php/Mushroom\" title=\"Mushroom\">Mushroom</a>, Clarice was the lover of <a href=\"/index.php/George_Graceford\" title=\"George Graceford\">George Graceford</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Holyhall\" title=\"Lord of Holyhall\">Lord of Holyhall</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Confessor\" title=\"Lord Confessor\">Lord Confessor</a>, and was aroused by <a href=\"/index.php/Torture\" title=\"Torture\">torture</a>, sometimes joining Lord Graceford in the dungeons to assist him in his work.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Clarice_Osgrey&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Clarice was the widowed aunt of <a href=\"/index.php/Unwin_Peake\" title=\"Unwin Peake\">Unwin Peake</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Starpike\" title=\"Lord of Starpike\">Lord of Starpike</a>. It is unknown if she was a maternal or paternal aunt, and whether she was an <a href=\"/index.php/House_Osgrey\" title=\"House Osgrey\">Osgrey</a> by birth or by marriage. When her nephew became <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/133_AC\" title=\"133 AC\">133&#160;AC</a>, he brought his own trusted kin to court, and Unwin put Clarice in charge of Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaera_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaera Targaryen\">Jaehaera Targaryen</a>'s household, supervising her maids, servants, and <a href=\"/index.php/Lady_companion\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Lady companion\">lady companions</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> After Jaehaera's death in the 9th moon of <a href=\"/index.php/133_AC\" title=\"133 AC\">133&#160;AC</a>, Clarice managed the household of the new queen, <a href=\"/index.php/Daenaera_Velaryon\" title=\"Daenaera Velaryon\">Daenaera Velaryon</a>, and stayed in her position after her nephew resigned as Hand in <a href=\"/index.php/134_AC\" title=\"134 AC\">134&#160;AC</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_voyage_of_alyn_oakenfist.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_voyage_of_alyn_oakenfist.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/index.php/135_AC\" title=\"135 AC\">135&#160;AC</a>, the king and queen suffered an attempted <a href=\"/index.php/Poison\" title=\"Poison\">poisoning</a>, and a <a href=\"/index.php/Secret_siege\" title=\"Secret siege\">conspiracy was made to frame</a> Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Larra_Rogare\" title=\"Larra Rogare\">Larra Rogare</a>, the wife of Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Viserys_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Viserys II Targaryen\">Viserys Targaryen</a>. When the conspirators were exposed, three of the queen's ladies were accused of being among them. Clarice was also suspected, as she supervised the ladies in Daenaera's household, and was well-acquainted with all the confessed conspirators, including George Graceford. If Clarice had been involved, it was likely Unwin Peake had been in the conspiracy as well. However, the three accused ladies, <a href=\"/index.php/Cassandra_Baratheon\" title=\"Cassandra Baratheon\">Cassandra Baratheon</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lucinda_Penrose\" title=\"Lucinda Penrose\">Lucinda Penrose</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Priscella_Hogg\" title=\"Priscella Hogg\">Priscella Hogg</a>, all denied Clarice's involvement, only shaking their heads when asked directly.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Behind_the_Scenes\">Behind the Scenes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Clarice_Osgrey&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Behind the Scenes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Clarice Osgrey, aunt to Unwin Peake, is a reference to Clarice Groan, aunt to the main character of the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gormenghast_(series)\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Gormenghast (series)\"><i>Gormenghast</i> series</a> by <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mervyn_Peake\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Mervyn Peake\">Mervyn Peake</a>. Peake's books are among <a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a>'s reading recommendations.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Clarice_Osgrey&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, The Lysene Spring and the End of Regency.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, Under the Regents - War and Peace and Cattle Shows.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_voyage_of_alyn_oakenfist.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_voyage_of_alyn_oakenfist.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, Under the Regents - The Voyage of Alyn Oakenfist.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">The Citadel: <a class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.westeros.org/Citadel/FAQ/Entry/Are_there_any_nods_to_other_works_in_the_series\">Are there any nods to other works in the series?</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/index.php/Not_a_Blog\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=